Thanks for taking the time to report this.

Can you please attach an example that shows the issue or missing feature?  (Must be openly licensed, completely self-contained so can directly run what you provide. Ideally use test_regress format, see https://veripool.org/guide/latest/contributing.html?highlight=test_regress#reporting-bugs)

What output from that test indicates it is wrong, and what is the correct or expected output?  (Or, please make test self-checking if possible.)
Verilator crashes due to a UAP when run without --debug. When run with --debug, Verilator asserts. See test in the linked PR.

What 'verilator' command line do we use to run your example?

```
verilator --cc --timing -Wno-fatal testcase/min_uaf_repro_real.sv
```

What 'verilator --version' are you using?  Did you try it with the git master version?  Did you try it with other simulators?
I'm using latest on `master`.

What OS and distribution are you using? Ubuntu 24.04

May we assist you in trying to fix this in Verilator yourself? Yes -- see linked PR.

(Please avoid attaching screenshots that show text - you can convert images to text using e.g. https://ocr.space)

```verilog
package p;
  typedef chandle PyObject;

  class uvm_object;
  endclass

  class py_object;
    function new(PyObject o);
    endfunction
  endclass

  class pyhdl_uvm_object_rgy;
    static pyhdl_uvm_object_rgy m_inst;
    static function pyhdl_uvm_object_rgy inst();
      if (m_inst == null) m_inst = new;
      return m_inst;
    endfunction
    function PyObject wrap(uvm_object obj);
      // Not important; just needs to be a non-void function
      if (obj == null) return null;
      return null;
    endfunction
  endclass

  class comp_proxy;
    virtual function PyObject get_config_object(string name, bit clone=0);
      uvm_object obj;
      py_object py_obj;
      bit has = 0;

      // This matches the original failing pattern:
      // - function call inside constructor arg (m_inNew)
      // - the whole branch becomes dead once `has` is constant-propagated
      if (has && obj != null) begin
        py_obj = new(pyhdl_uvm_object_rgy::inst().wrap(obj));
      end

      return null;
    endfunction
  endclass
endpackage

module top;
  import p::*;
  initial begin
    comp_proxy cp = new;
    void'(cp.get_config_object("x"));
    $finish;
  end
endmodule

```

